- "researcher_id" is a unique identifier for each researcher;
- "project_name" is the name of the project;
- "total_uploads" represents the total number of data uploads for each project;
- "avg_file_size" is the average size of the uploaded files;
- "interaction_type_name" describes the type of interaction (e.g., HBOND, Ionic);
- "access_count" is the number of times each interaction type has been accessed;
- "property_name" is the name of the property (e.g., molecular weight, isoelectric point);
- "property_count" is the number of properties recorded for each project.

sql:
SELECT AVG(CAST(property_value AS FLOAT)) AS average_molecular_weight
FROM protein_properties
WHERE property_name = 'molecular weight';

